{"aggregateId":{"id":"chat/chat-95735B24","kind":"workItem"},"body":{"agentMessage":{"excerpt":"Here's the full picture:\n\n---\n\n## Project: **Vokda** (`iksnae/vokda`)\n\n**Vokda is the central destination for everything TTS** — a voice discovery and curation app. Think Pinterest for voices: browse, play, pin, organize, and export across 25 providers and 550 voices in 53 languages.\n\n### Stack\n| Layer | Tech |\n|-------|------|\n| Frontend | SvelteKit 4 (TypeScript, static adapter) on AWS Amplify |\n| Backend | SAM-deployed serverless (API Gateway + Lambda, Node 20) |\n| Data | AppSync + DynamoDB (12 tables), Cognito auth |\n| Audio | S3 (`vokda-audio-bucket`) for synthesized clips |\n| API Domain | `api.vokda.iksnae.com` |\n\n### Current State (March 2026)\n- **550 voices** across **25 providers**, 100% sample coverage\n- **9 synthesis adapters** (OpenAI, ElevenLabs, Deepgram, Gemini TTS, Cartesia, LMNT, GCP TTS, Azure Speech, AWS Polly)\n- SSML visual editor (7 tags, real-time validation)\n- Collections, favorites, cart + Voice Pack export, BYOK key management\n- **178 unit tests** passing\n- Auth live: visitor → guest → curator → admin hierarchy\n\n### Open Work\n| # | Type | Title | Phase |\n|---|------|-------|-------|\n| **#54** | Issue | Add `estimateReadingTime(text)` to text-utilities | `agencyx:review` |\n| **#55** | PR | AgencyX delivery — sweep-build-54 | Open (from #54 build) |\n| #1 | Issue | 🏭 Factory Roadmap | tracking |\n| #2 | Issue | 🏭 Curator Proposals | tracking |\n\nIssue #54 is the active work item — a small utility function that composes on `wordCount` to estimate reading time. The build PR (#55) is up for review.\n\n---\n\n## My Capabilities\n\nI'm the **Foreman** — your interface to the agency. Here's what I can do:\n\n### 🔍 Inspect & Understand\n- **Read/search the codebase** — read files, search text/code, find symbol definitions and references\n- **Recall the shadow brain** — see everything the agency has decided across this engagement\n- **Read GitHub issues/PRs** in full, check CI status\n\n### 📋 Manage Work\n- **Create + queue issues** — file new work as scoped GitHub issues and kick them into the agency's pipeline\n- **Move issues through phases** (`new → product → planning → planned → ready → building → review → done`)\n- **Comment, close, reopen, assign, edit issues**\n- **Open PRs** for finished work\n\n### 🧠 Run Workflows\n- **`gate`** — Stage-1 intake: plan → verify → judge\n- **`planning`** — a validated plan\n- **`product`** — frame the product decision\n\n### 🛠 Skills (loadable playbooks)\n- **`geo-audit`** — Audit a product/site for AI-assistant discoverability (GEO)\n\n### 📝 Record & Remember\n- **`record_decision`** — durable journal of what was decided and why\n- **`record_engagement_history`** — client-clean narrative of what was delivered\n\n### 🔧 Direct Edits (trivial/immediate only)\n- Write/edit files for small, explicit operator requests (anything substantial gets filed as an issue for the agency to build)\n\n---\n\nWhat would you like to tackle?","workItemId":"chat/chat-95735B24"}},"contentHash":{"algorithm":"sha256","value":"f71632ad92ade1bf7c9c8a569d4b41799e3b53257e5317cfb15ae9654c2c3986"},"correlationId":"chat-95735B24","idempotencyKey":"chat-95735B24/activity/56","occurredAt":1782917655986.974,"schemaVersion":2,"sequence":56}
